          Season 1 overview
          The first season of the American sitcom The Big Bang Theory was originally aired on CBS from September 24, 2007, to May 19, 2008, over 17 episodes. An unaired pilot also exists. The Season 1 DVD came without a gag reel and is, so far, the only Big Bang Theory DVD set not to have one. Wikipedia
          Season 1 episodes
          S01 E17 The Tangerine Factor
          19 May 2008
          Watch
          Penny's break-up spurs Leonard to summon the courage to ask her out. Before the big night, each of them go to Sheldon for advice on what could a make or break the date.
          S01 E16 The Peanut Reaction
          12 May 2008
          Watch
          Penny learns that Leonard does not celebrate birthdays, so she plans a surprise party; Sheldon unexpectedly gets to live out one of his biggest fantasies in an electronics store.
          S01 E15 The Pork Chop Indeterminacy
          5 May 2008
          Watch
          Leonard devises a plan to eliminate his rivals when he, Wolowitz and Koothrappali all fall for Sheldon's twin sister, but his plan backfires when Sheldon decides to choose who his sister dates.
          S01 E14 The Nerdvana Annihilation
          28 Apr 2008
          Watch
          When Penny makes fun of Leonard's habit of collecting goofy memorabilia, he decides that it's time to give up his guilty pleasure, but Leonard's friends kick up a fuss and try to keep Leonard on the side of the nerds.
          S01 E13 The Bat Jar Conjecture
          21 Apr 2008
          Watch
          When Sheldon tries to prove his mental superiority as they train for the Physics Bowl, the guys kick him off the team and bring his nemesis (Sara Gilbert) aboard.
          S01 E12 The Jerusalem Duality
          14 Apr 2008
          Watch
          When Sheldon meets Dennis, a 15-year-old physicist who is clearly much brighter than he is, his confidence is so badly shaken that Leonard agrees to help him discredit the precocious teenager's research.
          S01 E11 The Pancake Batter Anomaly
          31 Mar 2008
          Watch
          Without having a clue what she has let herself in for, Penny volunteers to nurse Sheldon when he's sick. However, his friends know how miserable he is when he's ill and stay well away from him.
          S01 E10 The Loobenfeld Decay
          24 Mar 2008
          Watch
          Leonard and Sheldon each tell a lie to avoid going to see Penny on stage singing in a production of `Rent'. However, Sheldon's lie grows out of control, becoming too complicated for its own good.
          S01 E09 The Cooper-Hofstadter Polarization
          17 Mar 2008
          Watch
          When they're invited to give a presentation at a physics conference, Sheldon's reluctance to share the credit leads to a tiff between him and Leonard, and Penny's intervention only exacerbates the situation.
          S01 E08 The Grasshopper Experiment
          12 Nov 2007
          Watch
          Koothrappali becomes overwhelmed with panic when his parents arrange a blind date for him, only to discover that he actually can talk to a member of the opposite sex after a few drinks.
          S01 E07 The Dumpling Paradox
          5 Nov 2007
          Watch
          When Howard seduces Penny's friend and they spend the night together in Penny's flat, Penny asks to sleep on Leonard and Sheldon's sofa, so the guys ask her to fill in for Howard on one of their Halo teams.
          S01 E06 The Middle Earth Paradigm
          29 Oct 2007
          Watch
          Penny hosts a Halloween party, putting Leonard, Sheldon, Wolowitz and Koothrappali through a new test of their social skills.
          S01 E05 The Hamburger Postulate
          22 Oct 2007
          Watch
          Leonard fears that he's wasting his time on Penny, so he ends up making a connection with Leslie. Meanwhile, Sheldon frets over a change to his hamburger routine.
          S01 E04 The Luminous Fish Effect
          15 Oct 2007
          Watch
          Getting fired gives Sheldon the opportunity to explore life beyond physics, but when he spends his time weaving ponchos and acting like a shut-in, Leonard calls Sheldon's mother for assistance.
          S01 E03 The Fuzzyboots Corollary
          8 Oct 2007
          Watch
          Leonard is depressed when he discovers that Penny is dating someone. As a result, and encouraged by his friends and fellow scientists, Leonard actually summons up the courage to ask a woman out on a date.
          S01 E02 The Big Bran Hypothesis
          1 Oct 2007
          Watch
          Sheldon and Leonard go to Penny's apartment to drop off a package, but Sheldon can't believe how messy her apartment is.
          S01 E01 Pilot
          24 Sept 2007
          Watch
          Two physicists learn how little they know about life when a beautiful woman comes into their lives. When Leonard and Sheldon meet Penny, Leonard is immediately interested in her, but Sheldon feels his friend is chasing a dream he'll never catch.

          Why Big Bang was Cancelled?
          As it turned out, The Big Bang Theory was never canceled. The decision was primarily influenced by Jim Parsons' refusal to renew his $50 million contract for seasons 13 and 14. Even though he loved embodying Sheldon Cooper, eventually he grew exhausted and fearful of what life had to offer him beyond the sitcom.12-Jan-2022

          Description

          The lives of four socially awkward friends, Leonard, Sheldon, Howard and Raj, take a wild turn when they meet the beautiful and free-spirited Penny.
          First episode date: 24 September 2007
          Final episode date: 16 May 2019
          Theme song: Big Bang Theory Theme
          Writers: Chuck Lorre, Bill Prady, Maria Ferrari, Steven Molaro, MORE
          Awards: Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actor in a Comedy Series, MORE
          Genres: Sitcom, Television comedy
